remission at 5 y. The group", "bbox": [252.5, 599.7, 705.3, 613.6]}, {"text": "with remission at baseline and year 1 also evidenced lower mortality (3.2%) over 5 y compared", "bbox": [252.5, 616.1, 723.1, 630.1]}, {"text": "with those with remission at baseline only (5.0%) and those with remission at year 1 only", "bbox": [252.5, 632.5, 695.5, 646.5]}, {"text": "(5.3%). Mortality was significantly lower in all groups demonstrating remission at any time", "bbox": [252.5, 648.9, 706.3, 662.9]}, {"text": "point compared to the group who met criteria for CKD at both baseline and year 1 (15.7%; log-", "bbox": [252.5, 665.3, 726.2, 679.3]}, {"text": "rank test p < 0.001).", "bbox": [252.5, 681.8, 354.1, 695.7]}, {"text": "Sensitivity Analysis", "bbox": [252.5, 717.3, 379.6, 734.7]}, {"text": "Repeat analyses using the MDRD formula to estimate GFR revealed similar numbers of partici-", "bbox": [252.5, 742.0, 727.2, 756.0]}, {"text": "pants reaching each outcome. Predictors of different outcomes were similar using MDRD", "bbox": [252.5, 758.4, 699.0, 772.4]}, {"text": "eGFR to those presented above using CKD-EPI eGFR (S1–S4 Tables).", "bbox": [252.5, 774.9, 600.0, 788.8]}, {"text": "Discussion", "bbox": [252.5, 810.0, 332.5, 827.8]}, {"text": "In this population with CKD stage 3 in primary care, the majority of whom did not meet crite-", "bbox": [252.5, 835.2, 723.1, 849.1]}, {"text": "ria for referral to a nephrologist [13], we observed a very low incidence of ESKD over 5 y", "bbox": [252.5, 851.6, 693.1, 865.5]}, {"text": "(0.2%), and only a minority evidenced progression of CKD as defined by KDIGO (17.7%). Sim-", "bbox": [252.5, 868.0, 727.3, 882.0]}, {"text": "ilar to population-based studies, the risk of all-cause (14.2%) and cardiovascular mortality", "bbox": [252.5, 884.4, 700.5, 898.4]}, {"text": "PLOS Medicine | DOI:10.1371/journal.pmed.1002128 September 20, 2016 9 / 16", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}